    "history": {
        "short_description": "Built in 1903, Kannur Lighthouse is Kerala's first lighthouse, offering stunning coastal views from the top.",
        "detailed": "Kannur Lighthouse is one of the most iconic landmarks on Kerala's northern coast. Constructed initially by the British in 1903, it guided ships arriving at Kannur's busy port, which was historically a major spice and trade center. The current lighthouse tower stands 75 feet tall and uses an advanced rotating beacon system. The lighthouse complex includes a heritage museum showcasing maritime equipment, photographs, and lighthouse technology. Surrounded by well-maintained gardens, it is a favorite spot for tourists and photographers."
